        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "The transpose AT of a matrix A = [ak] is AT = [ajk]; rows become columns and conversely (Sec. 7.2). Here, A need not be square. If it is and A = AT, then A is called symmetric; if A = -AT, it is called skew-symmetric.",
        "bbox": [
          0.052,
          0.22933333333333333,
          0.9546666666666667,
          0.44355555555555554
        ],
        "order": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "mineru_PPT_ch7_page_142_3",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "For a product, (AB)T = BTAT (Sec. 7.2).",
        "bbox": [
          0.056666666666666664,
